    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-24T16:01:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-24T16:01:00-05:00" n="272"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–2453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Turkey</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-24T17:01:00-04:00"
                            >September 24, 1953—5:01 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>325. <persName corresp="#p_SARPERSR1">Sarper</persName> has informed our <gloss
                        target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss> Delegation that, in view of disclosure
                    yesterday of Philippine candidacy for <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> seat
                    sought by Turkey, he has cabled Ankara asking authority to announce at
                    appropriate time that Turkey will resign its <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1"
                        >ECOSOC</gloss> seat if elected to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>If you are approached by <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>, you may
                    confirm that we think such action would be helpful to Turkish <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> candidacy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
